<p><code>function f1()</code> ..>  Light Red Box</p>

<p><code>function f2()</code> ..>  Red Small Box</p>

<p>Here we have two functions, <code>f1()</code> and <code>f2()</code>. f2() is inner to f1().
f1() has a variable, <code>var x = 10</code>.</p>

<p>When invoking the function <code>f1()</code>, <code>f2()</code> can access the value of <code>var x = 10</code>.</p>

<p>Here is the code:</p>

<pre><code>function f1() {
    var x=10;

    function f2() {
        console.log(x)
    }

    return f2

}
f1()
</code></pre>

<p><code>f1()</code> invoking here:</p>

